title: After a three
text: • 1580 – After a three-day siege, the English Army beheads over 600 people, including papal soldiers and civilians, at Dún an Óir, Ireland.

title: The Western Union Cable Office in North Sydney, Nova Scotia, receives a top

title: With the rollout of the North American Numbering Plan, direct
text: • 1951 – With the rollout of the North American Numbering Plan, direct-dial coast-to-coast telephone service begins in the United States.
